"{\"uid\": \"cnbc.com-2024-08-02-simone-biles-trump-olympics-black-job.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  American gymnastSimone Bilesappeared to take a swipe at former PresidentDonald Trumpon Friday morning, tweeting \\\"I love my black job\\\" after winning hersecond individual all-around gold medalat theParis Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999912939465172, \"rank\": 8.60795454396133e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles' post on the social media platform X seemed to reference Trump's recent controversial comments that immigrants are \\\"taking Black jobs.\\\"\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 278, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999989049684, \"rank\": 9.830941589213735e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheRepublican presidential nomineehad said, \\\"They are taking Black jobs now and it could be 18, it could be 19 and even 20 million people,\\\" during his June 27debateagainst PresidentJoe Biden.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are taking Black jobs, and they are taking Hispanic jobs, and you have not seen it yet, but you are going to see something that's going to be the worst in our history,\\\" Trump said.\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9994073187264458, \"rank\": 0.0005930327528353834, \"text\": \"Hispanic\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999989049684, \"rank\": 9.830941589213735e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Data does not supportTrump's claim that immigrants are \\\"taking\\\" jobs from American workers.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 813, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999912939465172, \"rank\": 8.60795454396133e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CNBC has requested comment from Trump's campaign about Biles' tweet.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 832, \"end\": 836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3881201069073923e-13, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999989049684, \"rank\": 9.830941589213735e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump was asked on Wednesday to clarify what he meant by \\\"Black jobs\\\" in a Q&A session with three reporters at theNational Association of Black Journalists' annual convention.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999989049684, \"rank\": 9.830941589213735e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview\", \"score\": 0.9999729498347459, \"rank\": 2.7050897165295458e-05, \"text\": \"Q&A\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A Black job is anybody that has a job,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what it is.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1149, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anybody that has - they are taking the employment away from Black people.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are coming in, and they are coming in, they are invading.\\\"\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the same session, Trump also questioned Vice PresidentKamala Harris' race, falsely suggesting that the de facto Democratic presidential nominee has not always presented herself as Black.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1314, \"end\": 1319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999989049684, \"rank\": 9.830941589213735e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1408, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 0.7388660480273209, \"rank\": 0.20528822292661647, \"text\": \"Democratic\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She was always of Indian heritage and she was only promoting Indian heritage,\\\" Trump said.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.6131501591953666, \"rank\": 0.6294238110961083, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.6131501591953666, \"rank\": 0.6294238110961083, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999989049684, \"rank\": 9.830941589213735e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not know she was Black until a number of years ago, when she happened to turn Black and now she wants to be known as Black.\\\"\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Harris' father, who is Black, is from Jamaica.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.995026738359645, \"rank\": 0.003984050672415544, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her late mother was from India.\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9300020467771011, \"rank\": 0.06254094665446344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harris attended Howard University in Washington, D.C., one of the most well-known historically Black universities.\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999999654392, \"rank\": 2.9656011397540226e-11, \"text\": \"Howard University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_University\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9258741343396089, \"rank\": 0.079794548237527, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9998001651095954, \"rank\": 0.00019970441899006222, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9998001651095954, \"rank\": 0.00019970441899006222, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles, who is widely seen as the greatest American gymnast of all time, won her second individual all-around gold medal in Paris on Thursday.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999912939465172, \"rank\": 8.60795454396133e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999996763340802, \"rank\": 3.236661752522334e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With nine Olympic medals, six of them gold, Biles is the most decorated U.S. gymnast in history.\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is also the first American to win the individual gold more than once, and the first Olympic gymnast ever to win two in nonconsecutive Games.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2167, \"end\": 2175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999912939465172, \"rank\": 8.60795454396133e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her success in her third Olympics is the culmination of a three-year-long comeback story.\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles withdrew from the team final at the Olympic Games in Tokyo in 2021 after struggling with the \\\"twisties,\\\" which occur when a gymnast loses spatial awareness while in the air.\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999602307393739, \"rank\": 3.9347073276667545e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her withdrawal sparked a national conversation about mental health, but alsodrewcriticism.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"America hates me.\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world is going to hate me.\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can only see what they are saying on Twitter right now,\\\"Biles said on a podcast in April, recalling how she felt after the 2021 Games.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 0.9999999100346071, \"rank\": 8.996546181152852e-08, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One critic of Biles at the time was Sen.JD Vance, the Ohio Republican who is now Trump's running mate.\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2886, \"end\": 2891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.664030020015596e-13, \"text\": \"Vance\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\"}, {\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\", \"score\": 0.9999907502329155, \"rank\": 8.776393527809725e-06, \"text\": \"Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\",